/* Header Start*/
Before starting making our e-commerce website we will need a navigation bar which contain: logo, Home, Shop, Blog, About, contact and shopping logo. By default this are not styling. So to allow item to be display in on row we use mainly:
display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
And now to allow our list of item in the navbar to be in a same line we use display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;

IMPORTANT: the display: flex is the main css style that align item into just one line(row).

We also remove the point in the list and the underline we select li from the #header and set list-style: none then do the same for a from the  #header and set text-decoration: none.